LeetCode Problem 50: Pow(x, n)

Difficulty: Medium

ğŸ§  Problem Statement:
Implement pow(x, n), which calculates 
 (x raised to the power n).

ğŸ‘‰ Key Points:

You cannot use built-in power functions (x ** n or pow(x, n) in Python).

Need to handle:
Positive exponent
Negative exponent (result = 
Zero exponent (always 1)

	â€‹

ğŸ“ Code:
class Solution:
    def myPow(self, x: float, n: int) -> float:
        def fastPow(x, n):
            if n == 0:
                return 1
            half = fastPow(x, n // 2)
            if n % 2 == 0:
                return half * half
            else:
                return half * half * x

        if n < 0:        # negative exponent
            x = 1 / x
            n = -n
        return fastPow(x, n)


ğŸ” Dry Run:
Input: x = 2, n = 10
fastPow(2,10) â†’ even â†’ fastPow(2,5) squared
fastPow(2,5) â†’ odd â†’ fastPow(2,2) squared Ã— 2
fastPow(2,2) â†’ even â†’ fastPow(2,1) squared
fastPow(2,1) â†’ odd â†’ fastPow(2,0) squared Ã— 2
fastPow(2,0) = 1
Final Result: 
2^10=1024


ğŸ“Š Time Complexity:
-O(log n) â†’ because exponent is divided by 2 each step.

ğŸ§  Space Complexity:
-O(log n) recursion stack.
-Can be reduced to O(1) using iterative version.
